Delbert Dean BROWN v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 5866. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. July 8, 1958. Roehm A. West, Jr., Tulsa, Okl., for appellant. Frank D. McSherry, U. S. Atty., Harry G. Fender, Asst. U. S. Atty., and Paul M. Brewer, Asst. U. S. Atty., Muskogee, Okl., for appellee.

Before BRATTON, Chief Judge, and PICKETT, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
